<div class="container">

        <header class="header">
                <h1>Notification Templates Management</h1>
            </header>
    <!-- Section: Introduction -->
    <section class="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            In a business environment where responsiveness and communication are major assets, managing <strong>notification templates is an essential strategic tool.</strong> Movelys' dedicated module allows businesses to automate and personalize messages sent to their customers, suppliers, or internal users while ensuring consistency and efficiency in communications.
        </p>
        <p>
            Through a simple yet professional interface, users can configure different types of notifications - by email or SMS - for each key event in the management cycle: order confirmation, invoice sending, payment receipt, stock alerts, payment reminders, etc. Each template can be customized with preferred tone and content, with the ability to insert <strong>dynamic variables (customer name, sale date, amount due, etc.)</strong>, ensuring automatic message personalization.
        </p>
        <p>
            By centralizing and standardizing communications, Movelys improves <strong>customer relationships, deadline management, and strengthens the company's professional credibility.</strong> This module offers significant time savings while ensuring reliable, automated information dissemination at each operational process stage.
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 1: Notification Templates -->
    <section class="notification-models">
        <h2>1) Notification Templates</h2>

        <div class="subsection">
            <h3>1.1) Purpose of This Interface</h3>
            <p>
                The <strong>Notification Templates interface in Movelys allows you to</strong> <strong>configure, customize, and automate messages sent to your customers or suppliers.</strong> These messages can be sent automatically for events like a <strong>sale, payment, order, or reservation.</strong>
            </p>
            <p>These messages can be sent:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>By email</li>
                <li>By SMS</li>
                <li>By WhatsApp</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
            <h3>1.2) Section-by-Section Explanation</h3>

            <div class="sub-subsection">
                <h4>1.2.1) Main Section: General Template</h4>
                <p><strong>Title: Send General Ledger</strong></p>
                <p>
                    This means the template is designed for automatic sending of the accounting general ledger (account report) by email.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Available Tags</strong><br>
                        These are keywords in brackets like <code>[business.name]</code> or <code>[balance due].</code> When the message is sent, these tags are automatically replaced with company or customer information. For example:<br>
                        - <code>[Business.name]</code> → "Scent & Vitality"<br>
                        - <code>[Balance due]</code> → "XOF 20,000"
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Email Subject:</strong><br>
                        This is the email title that will appear in the recipient's inbox (e.g., "Your Monthly General Ledger").
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>CC (Carbon Copy) / BCC (Blind Carbon Copy):</strong><br>
                        - <strong>CC:</strong> recipients added here will see the message and other recipients.<br>
                        - <strong>BCC:</strong> recipients added here will receive the email invisibly to others.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Email Body</strong><br>
                        Area where you write the main message content. This is where you place personalized text, using tags when needed.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="sub-subsection">
                <h4>1.2.2. Section: Customer Notifications</h4>
                <p>
                    This section allows automatically sending messages to <strong>customers based on specific actions.</strong>
                </p>
                <p>❖ <strong>Available Tabs:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>New Sale:</strong> when a purchase is made</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment Received:</strong> when a customer pays</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment Reminder:</strong> payment reminder</li>
                    <li><strong>New Reservation:</strong> to confirm a reservation</li>
                    <li><strong>New Quote:</strong> to automatically send a quote</li>
                </ul>
                <p>❖ <strong>Field Details:</strong></p>
                <table class="component-table">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Available Tags</th>
                        <th>List of tags that can be used to automatically insert information into the message.</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Email Subject</th>
                        <th>The title visible in the customer's inbox (e.g., "Thank you for your order!").</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>CC / BCC</th>
                        <th>Secondary recipients who are visible (CC) or invisible (BCC).</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Email Body</th>
                        <th>Customized text with tags</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>SMS Body</th>
                        <th>Short version of the message sent via SMS.</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>WhatsApp Text</th>
                        <th>Message that will be automatically sent via WhatsApp.</th>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <p>❖ <strong>Checkbox Options:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Auto Send Email: automatic email sending</li>
                    <li>Auto Send SMS: automatic SMS sending</li>
                    <li>Auto Send WhatsApp notification: automatic WhatsApp sending</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Example of automatically generated message:</strong></p>
                <blockquote>
                    <em>Dear Jean Dupont,</em><br>
                    <em>Your invoice #INV-0001 has been registered.</em><br>
                    <em>Amount paid: XOF 15,000</em><br>
                    <em>Thank you for your business.</em><br>
                    <em>Scent & Vitality</em>
                </blockquote>
            </div>

            <div class="sub-subsection">
                <h4>1.2.3. Section: Supplier Notifications</h4>
                <p>
                    This section allows automatically notifying suppliers in various situations.
                </p>
                <p>❖ <strong>Available Tabs:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>New Order:</strong> new purchase order</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment Made:</strong> payment made to supplier</li>
                    <li><strong>Items Received:</strong> product receipt</li>
                    <li><strong>Pending Items:</strong> pending products</li>
                    <li><strong>Purchase Order:</strong> purchase order</li>
                </ul>
                <p>❖ <strong>Configuration Elements:</strong></p>
                <table class="component-table">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Field</th>
                        <th>Explanation</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Available Tags</td>
                        <td>Supplier-specific tags</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Email Subject</td>
                        <td>Example: "New Order from Scent & Vitality"</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CC / BCC</td>
                        <td>Add other recipients as needed</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Email Body</td>
                        <td>Example: "Please deliver order ref. 0002 as soon as possible."</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>SMS Body</td>
                        <td>Summary message for SMS (shorter than email)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>WhatsApp Text</td>
                        <td>Message to send via WhatsApp</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <p>
                    <strong>System Alert: an orange message at the bottom informs that</strong><br>
                    <em>"the company logo doesn't work in SMS."</em><br>
                    This means you can include the company name, but not a logo in an SMS.
                </p>
                <p>❖ <strong>Action Button</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Save:</strong> this button saves all templates and settings you've defined on the page.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="sub-subsection">
                <h4>1.3) Why This Interface Is Important</h4>
                <table class="component-table">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Advantage</th>
                        <th>Explanation</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Time Savings</td>
                        <td>Messages are sent automatically without manual action.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Personalization</td>
                        <td>Each customer or supplier receives a message tailored to their situation.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Clear Communication</td>
                        <td>All parties receive the right information at the right time.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Multi-Channel</td>
                        <td>Ability to send messages via email, SMS or WhatsApp.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Fewer Errors</td>
                        <td>Tags automatically fill in the correct information.</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
